I’ve been asked so many times these past few weeks if I am going to ever compete in a body building show and the answer is… YES. I want to. I feel that I have the discipline to be able to. Right now, I am in a healing phase. I went through so much this past year & it changed so much of my life. I have been spending these past few months just trying to gather myself & get back to feeling like ME again. I’ve lost so much.. work, friends, opportunities, you name it, I’ve lost it. But I got to know Jesus this year. And I know the future is going to be amazing. No matter what has been taken, God is restoring & replacing. But yeah you guys, I am in a place where I am becoming the person that God intended me to be. Competition? GOD WILLING. 👀❤️ goodnight!

Most of us begin working out bc we wanna change the way we look. And that’s what everyone sees. The physical. However, you end up keeping up with your goals because of the changes you feel internally. Working out isn’t the most fun thing in the world. The fun part is when you fall in love with the pain. Then you realize how in order to grow we must go through pain.

Came across this shirt that I used to loveee. Threw it away, just like I threw all of my other wicked items. 🤣 I used to do some witch craft. Not much but I did dabble into it. I thought I had hidden spiritual gifts that I had to find so I would spend time trying to figure that out. I was so intrigued with being a psychic, reading minds, controlling things with my mind, trying out spells, ect. Yet, I was always seeing shadows and having sleep paralysis.. and more. (These kind of things open doors to you, and not the good kind) one random day I just decided to stop. Then one day, I began to read the Holy Bible. And in my searching of if God is real, I asked Jesus to show me if he is, and he held me all night and I slept so peacefully. I can never deny Jesus, he is my Lord and my savior. Life just isn’t the same as it was before and I am grateful for that. Deuteronomy 18:9-13 says, “When you enter the land the Lord your God is giving you, do not learn to imitate the detestable ways of the nations there. Let no one be found among you who sacrifices their son or daughter in the fire, who practices divination or sorcery, interprets omens, engages in witchcraft, or casts spells, or who is a medium or spiritist or who consults the dead. Anyone who does these things is detestable to the Lord; because of these same detestable practices the Lord your God will drive out those nations before you. You must be blameless before the Lord your God.” 
Now I am free. I am not perfect. But I am delivered from darkness. And waiting for the Lord Jesus return. 🫶 #christian #walkwithchrist #jesuschrist

Wear what makes you comfortable! Whether that’s a matching set, a hoodie & sweats, or whatever makes you comfortable! 🫶 Why I’ve decided to cover up more, lately. 
Well, I noticed that I was just going based off my body image, and surrounding my thoughts on that. How flat is my stomach today? How big are my glutes today? Do I look swole today? And really just caring too dang much about how my body looks. Which will affect the quality of my workout. Covering up just takes that pressure away of looking so “perfect”. I can zone in 100% of the time and get a killer workout! Humble myself and just the job done daily. Do I think I’m better than women who don’t cover up? Absolutely not. I will for sure be wearing my gym sets from time to time. This isn’t a sexual thing either because, I am not perverted and ran by lust. Which is actually another good reason to cover up, to help a brother or sister out if you’re that dang good looking! This topic, I can go in so deeply. However, there is no shame here. I love to share insight & appreciate those who have followed me on this journey on social media and now my journey as I get closer to Jesus! Love y’all! 💕
